@NODE "Configuration" "Configuration"



                               Configuration
                              ***************

          To configure NetFace just change the tooltypes arguments. 
          Supported tooltypes are:



 C4MAIL        - The command that you use too check on your server if you
                 have any way wait to be downloaded.

                 Eg. AmiTCP:Bin/finger cliffe@post


 FTP           - The name and location of your stand alone Ftp client.

                 Eg. AmiTCP:AmiFTP/AmiFTP


 GETNEWS       - The command that you use too collect your news items.
                 After using this button you can not use any thing else
                 on the NetFace window until GETNEWS has finished.
  
                @{fg shine} HINT. Launch a Web Browser first than GETNEWS that way @{fg text}
                       @{fg shine}you can use that while downloading news.@{fg text}
    
                 Eg. AmiTCP:Bin/nntptransfer

                 
 IRC           - Your choice of Internet Relay Chat program, You will need 
                 to use WBRun with this function or the program may crash
                 your choice of program.
  
                 Eg. WBRun AmiTCP:Grapevine/gv 


 MAIL          - Your choice of Mail program, If you use RUN >NIL: <NIL: 
                 before the program name the mail program does not open
                 another cli output window.
 
                 Eg. RUN >NIL: <NIL: AmiTCP:Bin/ADMail


 N-BROWSER     - Your choice of News Browser program, You will need to use 
                 WBRun with this function if you use NewsAgent.

                 Eg. WBRun AmiTCP:Bin/NewsAgent


 NEWS          - Your choice of News program, If you use RUN >NIL: <NIL: 
                 before the program name the News program does not open
                 another cli output window.

                 Eg. RUN >NIL: <NIL: AmiTCP:Bin/Grn height=540 width=704 
                 top=10 wrap=83 


 PREPNEWS      - This is the script that unbatches your news downloads
                 edit the last line of this script too your choice of
                 newsreader, Or use a script of your own choice.

                 Eg. AmiTCP:Bin/PrepNews


 NOREQUESTER   - If this tooltype is present there is no Quit Yes or NO
                 requester when you quit NetFace.


 USER1         - Use this button too launch a program that does not have
                 a button or if you want too use 2 different Web browser's.

                 Eg. cdrun AmiTCP:IBrowse/IBrowse


 USER1         - Use this button too launch a program that does not have
                 a button or if you want too use 2 different Mail programs.

                 Eg. AmiTCP:MetaTool/Metatool


 WEB           - Your choice of Web Browser.

                 Eg. AmiTCP:Bin/Amosaic-AmiTCP 
 

 AUTOLINK      - Use this button too launch an Auto link up script

                 Eg. AmiTCP:Bin/Link up News


 LINKD         - Use this button too launch your link down script.

                 Eg. AmiTCP:Bin/Link down


 LINKU         - Use this button too launch your link up script.

                 Eg. AmiTCP:Bin/Link up


 STARTN        - This is your script that runs AmiTCP and set's up
                 all your AmiTCP directory assignments.

                 Eg. Work:AmiTCP/Bin/StartNet

                 @{fg shadow}@{bg shine}IF THIS TOOLTYPE IS NOT SET AND/OR AMITCP@{fg text}@{bg background}
                   @{fg shadow}@{bg shine} CAN NOT START THE PROGRAM WILL QUIT.@{fg text}@{bg background}  
                         

 STOPN         - This is script command that stops AmiTCP.

                 Eg. AmiTCP:Bin/Stopnet




